reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good Video Card For Every Day Use
reviews.reviewText: I bought the QTHREE Geforce 210 1024 MB DDR3 Graphics Card as an experiment. I read an article on PC Magazine's website that said it is a good idea to use a video video card in all computers because the video card takes the burden of producing all video images off of the central processing chip. So I thought I would test that advice and purchase an inexpensive video card. I saw the QTHREE Geforce 210 1024 MB DDR3 Graphics Card here on the Amazon website and bought it. The QTHREE Geforce 210 helped to reduce video rendering times in my video editing software and online videos look good. But I was pleasantly surprised to find that the video card helped to reduce latency timing issues when using my MIDI DAW software virtual instruments. For less than $40 dollars I got a nice performance boost. The QTHREE Geforce 210 uses an older processing chip so performance would probably be greater by using a more up to date video card but the advice proved to be true. That is why serious video game players spent a lot of money buying high performance graphics cards for game play. But the QTHREE Geforce 210 works. Thanks Amazon for having such a wide variety of computer parts and accessories.

reviews.reviewTitle: Ideal para servidor pero un poco cara
reviews.reviewText: Lo compré para un servidor que necesitaba salida de video. Las tarjetas de video que tenian eran todas muy antiguas (PCIe v2) y ya no funcionaban. Es una pena que para poder sacar video de un servidor (para acceder a la bio o instalar el sistema operativo) tengamos que pagar tanto dinero pero es que parece que ya no se vendan tarjetas más baratas.En cualquier caso, a pesar de que la GT 210 sea tecnologia antigua, funciona correctamente en placas base modernas y el perfil bajo es necesario para su montaje.
